docs.name: Target Audience Identification
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to identify the target audience of your apps. This identification, in turn, will support the development of an app that directly fits the specific needs of the customer group.

docs.name: Persona Creation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create a concrete user persona out of the abstract gathered customer information. This, in turn, allows you to make first assumptions about the appâ€™s specific users and identify the ideal customer.

docs.name: Customer Journey Map Creation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to discover the behavior of the customer and analyze at which points he will interact with the app. This will help you to make assumptions about the user flow of the application.

docs.name: Trend Discovery
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to gather information about current trends in the industry. This could be a mix of new products, founded companies, or general ongoing trends.

docs.name: Store Trend Discovery
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to gather information about current trends in the stores. These could be recommended apps by the store provider or lists of top-downloaded or top-grossing apps. The discovery can be made by hand or with external tools.

docs.name: Keyword Discovery
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to discover possible problems and their solutions for different keywords in the area you want to develop an app for. The discovery can be made directly with the search engines or specific keyword tools.

docs.name: Store Keyword Discovery
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to discover apps and the problems they try to solve instead of the stores based on your own keywords. For this, you can discover the apps and their reviews directly or use a store analysis tool.

docs.name: Market Problem Observation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to observe an existing market to gather insights about current existing problems. This can be made by discovering existing processes or speaking directly to involved persons.

docs.name: Own Problem Observation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to observe problems in the own environment to identify the workarounds which are currently done to solve them. For this, you can discover for own life situation for a certain amount of time and note down repeating problems.

docs.name: Event Attention
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to discover problems from external persons or discuss potential ideas with other persons with the same interest. For this, you can attend different events like hackathons, startup meetings, or business conferences.

docs.name: Social Media Discovery
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to discover the problems of potential customers in social media posting. Social media websites have a mass amount of users who claim about possible problems in a daily manner.

docs.name: Online Community Discovery
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to discover the problems of potential customers in a specific niche. For this, online communities within this niche can be visited, and problems can be collected.

docs.name: Interview Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct interviews with single persons. Single Interviews can be used to get a deeper understanding of the problem and validate possible steps during the business model development process.

docs.name: Group Interview Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct group interviews with different persons. Group interviews can be used to discover and analyze problems of different persons at a single time and validate possible steps during the development at a single time.

docs.name: Customer Interview Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct interviews with potential customers of the app. The interviews can be used to discover and analyze the current problems or validate different steps of the development process.

docs.name: Survey Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different persons. Surveys can be used to research a high number of persons with standardized questions about the problem, possible ideas, or different developed prototypes.

docs.name: Social Media Survey Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different customers on social media websites. Social media surveys allow discovering a high number of results for mass-market apps.

docs.name: Online Communities Survey Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different customers in online communities. Forums allow discovering a medium number of specific results for niche market apps.

docs.name: Market Potential Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the potential size of the target market. The goal is to identify a marketâ€™s high growth potential together with growth drivers and possible barriers.

docs.name: Keyword Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the traffic and results for specific keywords that target your customer and problem. With the help of keyword analysis, it is possible to look if many such people are searching for the problem and can be therefore targeted with search engine optimization.

docs.name: Store Keyword Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the traffic and results for specific keywords within the stores. With the help of keyword analysis, it is possible to look if many such people are searching for the problem and which solutions are currently offered.

docs.name: Competitor Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify target customers and used features to create a competitive advantage.

docs.name: Store Competitor Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the store competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify target customers and used features to create a competitive advantage.

docs.name: Store Competitor Feature Set Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the store competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify the commonly used features.

docs.name: Store Competitor Business Model Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the store competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify the commonly used parts of the business model.

docs.name: Problem Sharping
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to sharp the problem after the analysis of the market and the competitors. This, in turn, should help to concentrate on a single concrete problem instead of trying to solve multiple problems at the same time.

docs.name: Target Group Sharping
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to sharp the target group after the analysis of the market and the competitors. This, in turn, should help to concentrate on a specific group instead of trying to solve the problem for multiple diverse groups.

docs.name: Feature Set Creation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create a set of features that the app should have. This set can be created out of the insights during the discovery and analysis phase.

docs.name: Value Proposition Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a value proposition for the customer. For this, a value proposition canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

docs.name: Business Model Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a business model for the app. For this, a business model canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

docs.name: Business Model Initialization Pattern
docs.description: This pattern allows the creation of a fixed process to create and validate a business model for a mobile application. Therefore, the process is particularly suitable for developers who have little experience with the creation of business models.

docs.name: Business Model Discovery Initialization Pattern
docs.description: This pattern allows the flexible creation of a process for business model development starting at the discovery phase. Due to this flexibility, it should be used only by experts in business model development.

docs.name: Monetization Strategy Identification
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to identify a monetization strategy for the app. This strategy, in turn, should ensure the sustainable development of the app over time.

docs.name: Marketing Strategy Identification
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to identify a marketing strategy for the app. This strategy, in turn, should ensure to reach potential customers with a corresponding sales funnel.

docs.name: Unique Selling Point Identification
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to identify a unique selling point for the app. This unique selling point, in turn, will ensure a competitive advantage against similar apps in the market.

docs.name: Feature Set Priorisation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to prioritize the feature set according to the most important features. This should ensure to consider only the most important features at the beginning of your app development.

docs.name: Hypothesis Priorisation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to prioritize the hypotheses inside your developed business model to find out the most important ones. The most important hypotheses should be tested at the beginning to ensure the development of a successful app.

docs.name: SWOT Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct to SWOT Analysis to identify the strength, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats of your application. This analysis can be used to improve the feature set and business model of the application.

docs.name: Metric Identification
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to identify important metrics to measure the success of the app. These metrics can be derived from the feature set and the business model of the application.

docs.name: Competitive Advantage Analysis
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the competitive advantage of the own application. This analysis, in turn, should ensure to focus on these advantages during the beginning of the development.

docs.name: Inbound Marketing Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct inbound marketing during the development phase. Inbound marketing means to active creation of valuable content that potential customers can discover during the search for solutions to their problems.

docs.name: Outbound Marketing Conduction
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct outbound marketing during the development phase. Outbound marketing means to direct push the potential customers to the current state of the solution.

docs.name: Website Creation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create a website to show the current state of the app. On the website, it is also possible to share valuable content related to the problem and the solution.

docs.name: Landing Page Creation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create a landing page to show the unique selling point of the app. The landing page can be used to analyze conversion rates of different UPSs and collect mail addresses for further interaction.

docs.name: Information Creation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create valuable information for the target customers on social media channels. This, in turn, helps to build a brand before starting with the product selling.

docs.name: Organic Traffic Generation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to generate organic traffic for the created content. This can be done by optimizing the content for search engines posting links to the content of social media platforms and forums.

docs.name: Inorganic Traffic Generation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to generate organic traffic for the created content. This can be done by optimizing the content for search engines posting links to the content of social media platforms and forums.

docs.name: Prototype Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a prototype of the app. This prototype can be created in various forms like sketches, mockups, wireframes, or clickable prototypes.

docs.name: Proof-of-Concept Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a proof-of-concept of the app. This should ensure the technical feasibility of developing the features of the app.

docs.name: Mockup Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create a mockup of the app. A mockup is a graphical representation to give the potential customer an impression of who the app will look like.

docs.name: Wireframe Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create a wireframe of the app. A wireframe is a visualization of the app that allows the potential customer to understand the navigation inside the app.

docs.name: MVP Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to create a minimum viable product of the app. An MVP is a small product that can be directly used by the potential customer to solve his problem.

docs.name: Platform Selection
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to select a platform where the app should be running. An app can be developed for a specific mobile platform or as a web app.

docs.name: Cost Estimation
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to estimate the costs that the development of the app will costs.

docs.name: Financing Search
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to clarify the finances of the app development.

docs.name: Internal Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to develop the first version of the app. Internal developers will do this development.

docs.name: External Development
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to develop the first version of the app. External developers will do this development.

docs.name: Platform Publishing
docs.description: The goal of this building block is to publish the product on the selected platforms.

method.name: Market Problem Observation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to observe an existing market to gather insights about current existing problems. This can be made by discovering existing processes or speaking directly to involved persons.

method.name: Store Trend Discovery
method.description: The goal of this building block is to gather information about current trends in the stores. These could be recommended apps by the store provider or lists of top-downloaded or top-grossing apps. The discovery can be made by hand or with external tools.

method.name: Interview Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct interviews with single persons. Single Interviews can be used to get a deeper understanding of the problem and validate possible steps during the business model development process.

method.name: Social Media Survey Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different customers on social media websites. Social media surveys allow discovering a high number of results for mass-market apps.

method.name: Market Potential Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the potential size of the target market. The goal is to identify a marketâ€™s high growth potential together with growth drivers and possible barriers.

method.name: Competitor Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify target customers and used features to create a competitive advantage.

method.name: Store Competitor Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the store competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify target customers and used features to create a competitive advantage.

method.name: Feature Set Creation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to create a set of features that the app should have. This set can be created out of the insights during the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Value Proposition Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a value proposition for the customer. For this, a value proposition canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Business Model Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a business model for the app. For this, a business model canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Competitive Advantage Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the competitive advantage of the own application. This analysis, in turn, should ensure to focus on these advantages during the beginning of the development.

method.name: Feature Set Priorisation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to prioritize the feature set according to the most important features. This should ensure to consider only the most important features at the beginning of your app development.

method.name: MVP Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to create a minimum viable product of the app. An MVP is a small product that can be directly used by the potential customer to solve his problem.

method.name: Group Interview Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct group interviews with different persons. Group interviews can be used to discover and analyze problems of different persons at a single time and validate possible steps during the development at a single time.

method.name: Inbound Marketing Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct inbound marketing during the development phase. Inbound marketing means to active creation of valuable content that potential customers can discover during the search for solutions to their problems.

method.name: MVP Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to create a minimum viable product of the app. An MVP is a small product that can be directly used by the potential customer to solve his problem.

method.name: Survey Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different persons. Surveys can be used to research a high number of persons with standardized questions about the problem, possible ideas, or different developed prototypes.

method.name: Platform Selection
method.description: The goal of this building block is to select a platform where the app should be running. An app can be developed for a specific mobile platform or as a web app.

method.name: Cost Estimation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to estimate the costs that the development of the app will costs.

method.name: Internal Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop the first version of the app. Internal developers will do this development.

method.name: Platform Publishing
method.description: The goal of this building block is to publish the product on the selected platforms.

method.name: Survey Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different persons. Surveys can be used to research a high number of persons with standardized questions about the problem, possible ideas, or different developed prototypes.

method.name: Target Audience Identification
method.description: The goal of this building block is to identify the target audience of your apps. This identification, in turn, will support the development of an app that directly fits the specific needs of the customer group.

evaluation.description: customer should be able to evaluate benefits of the application

after-sales.description: customer receives value after the purchase process

docs.description: Used to create the business models of the competitors to compare them, later, with the company's business model.

docs.name: Competitor Business Model Comparison
docs.description: Compare the business models of competitors against the company's own business model.

docs.description: Used to create the value propositions of the competitors to compare them, later, with the company's value proposition.

docs.name: Competitor Value Proposition Comparison

method.name: Value Proposition Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a value proposition for the customer. For this, a value proposition canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Competitor Value Proposition Analysis
method.description: Used to create the value propositions of the competitors to compare them, later, with the company's value proposition.

method.name: Competitor Value Proposition Comparison
method.description: Compare the value propositions of competitors against the company's own value proposition.

method.name: Business Model Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a business model for the app. For this, a business model canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Competitor Business Model Analysis
method.description: Used to create the business models of the competitors to compare them, later, with the company's business model.

method.name: Competitor Business Model Comparison
method.description: Compare the business models of competitors against the company's own business model.

method.name: Value Proposition Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a value proposition for the customer. For this, a value proposition canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Competitor Value Proposition Analysis
method.description: Used to create the value propositions of the competitors to compare them, later, with the company's value proposition.

method.name: Competitor Value Proposition Comparison
method.description: Compare the value propositions of competitors against the company's own value proposition.

method.name: Business Model Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a business model for the app. For this, a business model canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Competitor Business Model Analysis
method.description: Used to create the business models of the competitors to compare them, later, with the company's business model.

method.name: Competitor Business Model Comparison
method.description: Compare the business models of competitors against the company's own business model.

method.name: Market Problem Observation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to observe an existing market to gather insights about current existing problems. This can be made by discovering existing processes or speaking directly to involved persons.

method.name: Store Trend Discovery
method.description: The goal of this building block is to gather information about current trends in the stores. These could be recommended apps by the store provider or lists of top-downloaded or top-grossing apps. The discovery can be made by hand or with external tools.

method.name: Interview Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct interviews with single persons. Single Interviews can be used to get a deeper understanding of the problem and validate possible steps during the business model development process.

method.name: Social Media Survey Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different customers on social media websites. Social media surveys allow discovering a high number of results for mass-market apps.

method.name: Market Potential Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the potential size of the target market. The goal is to identify a marketâ€™s high growth potential together with growth drivers and possible barriers.

method.name: Competitor Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify target customers and used features to create a competitive advantage.

method.name: Store Competitor Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the store competitors based on the gained insights of customers and problems. The competitor analysis can be used to identify target customers and used features to create a competitive advantage.

method.name: Feature Set Creation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to create a set of features that the app should have. This set can be created out of the insights during the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Value Proposition Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a value proposition for the customer. For this, a value proposition canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Business Model Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop a business model for the app. For this, a business model canvas is filled out with the insights of the discovery and analysis phase.

method.name: Competitive Advantage Analysis
method.description: The goal of this building block is to analyze the competitive advantage of the own application. This analysis, in turn, should ensure to focus on these advantages during the beginning of the development.

method.name: Feature Set Priorisation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to prioritize the feature set according to the most important features. This should ensure to consider only the most important features at the beginning of your app development.

method.name: MVP Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to create a minimum viable product of the app. An MVP is a small product that can be directly used by the potential customer to solve his problem.

method.name: Group Interview Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct group interviews with different persons. Group interviews can be used to discover and analyze problems of different persons at a single time and validate possible steps during the development at a single time.

method.name: Inbound Marketing Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct inbound marketing during the development phase. Inbound marketing means to active creation of valuable content that potential customers can discover during the search for solutions to their problems.

method.name: MVP Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to create a minimum viable product of the app. An MVP is a small product that can be directly used by the potential customer to solve his problem.

method.name: Survey Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different persons. Surveys can be used to research a high number of persons with standardized questions about the problem, possible ideas, or different developed prototypes.

method.name: Platform Selection
method.description: The goal of this building block is to select a platform where the app should be running. An app can be developed for a specific mobile platform or as a web app.

method.name: Cost Estimation
method.description: The goal of this building block is to estimate the costs that the development of the app will costs.

method.name: Internal Development
method.description: The goal of this building block is to develop the first version of the app. Internal developers will do this development.

method.name: Platform Publishing
method.description: The goal of this building block is to publish the product on the selected platforms.

method.name: Survey Conduction
method.description: The goal of this building block is to conduct surveys with different persons. Surveys can be used to research a high number of persons with standardized questions about the problem, possible ideas, or different developed prototypes.

method.name: Target Audience Identification
method.description: The goal of this building block is to identify the target audience of your apps. This identification, in turn, will support the development of an app that directly fits the specific needs of the customer group.
